  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a machine-learning surrogate model trained to predict pump-induced hemolysis for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The ML model replaces a full CFD solve at inference time, predicting the relative hemolysis index (RH) across 5 flow-speed operating points. COU1 evaluates whether the ML surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. All validation results are drawn from a held-out test split of the same CFD-derived dataset used for training. No robustness, covariate-shift, or adversarial characterisation is included.",
