    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-ml-cpb-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-vv-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for MRL 2. The ML surrogate demonstrates strong nominal-condition predictive performance (R² 0.974, MAE 0.031 on the i.i.d. test set) and correctly identifies worst-case operating conditions in 98.75% of test cases. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per the ASME V&V 40 assessment matrix. The surrogate is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device under the defined COU.",
